Anthony Alfred Henley (7 November 1846 – 14 December 1916) was an English cricketer.
Henley represented Hampshire in one first-class match in 1866 against Surrey at the Kennington Oval.
Henley died in Woodbridge, Suffolk on 14 December 1916.

Francis Anthony Hoste Henley (11 February 1884 – 26 June 1963) was an English first-class cricketer active 1903–08 who played for Middlesex and Oxford University.Francis Henley at CricketArchive He was a son of Anthony Henley, who played cricket for Hampshire.

Henley was born  on 11 February 1884 in Woodbridge, Suffolk, and was educated at Oriel College, Oxford. He was a son of Anthony Henley, who played cricket for Hampshire. During World War I he was an officer in the Army Service Corps. In 1924 he wrote The Boys' Book of Cricket. He died on 26 June 1963 in Wheathampstead, aged 79 years old .
